post_text:
This Friday (8/28), Idalia’s Student Council is hosting a “COVID CAN’T…” walk for all interested 6th-12th students. Immediately following lunch (1pm) we will leave the school and begin our walk. Mrs. Ramseier (Student Council Sponsor), Mr. Johnson, and other Idalia staff members will participate and sponsor the walk. We will walk from the school to Mr. Weirich’s house turnoff (where there will be a water/refreshment break), before returning to the school (approximately 4 miles total) before school is out for the day.

*Friday’s forecast is calling for a high of 87 – students should wear comfortable clothes and shoes appropriate for a 4-mile walk.

**Any students choosing not to participate in the walk will have a teacher sponsored study hall.

post_text:
Why are we partnering with the Positive Coaching Alliance? "Isn't Positive Coaching just a lot of soft, happy talk?"

"No. Positive is Powerful. That’s why such accomplished coaches as Steve Kerr, Phil Jackson and dozens of other top pro and college coaches use our techniques and advise us on theirs as members of PCA’s National Advisory Board. Positive reinforcement and demonstration of belief in your athletes keeps them attuned to the necessary corrective criticism the best coaches provide. When coaches apply the right balance between specific, truthful praise and specific, constructive criticism they help athletes improve and compete better, while also helping them develop as people."

Idalia School wants successful programs and successful humans. #wolfpackstrong

Idalia Summer Weights and Conditioning is set to open on Monday, June 22nd!! It will run Mondays through Thursdays til August with 2 sessions each day capped at 22 athletes at each session. You will need to have the athlete sign up for a slot at https://www.signupgenius.com/go/70a0d4aa5ab2aa7fb6-idalia.

For the first week, Junior High and High School Boys will be from 6:00-6:40 am, while Junior High and High School Girls will be from 6:50-7:30 am. This will alternate each week.

Temperatures will be taken of each athlete upon entrance and sanitary measures are being taken to ensure a healthy environment.

post_text: Congratulations Mrs. Wright!
shared_text:
Morgan Community College- Burlington Center
January 6 at 12:33 PM ·

Please join us in congratulating Su Wright!! Ms. Wright has taught for Morgan Community College-Burlington Center for many years in English and Sociology.

From Jack Kroll, Associate Director of Transfer Admissions & Graduate Recruitment: "Su, Congratuations on being named a CU Boulder Outstanding Colorado Educator. We are proud & honored to extend you this recognition. Thanks for all that you do for students.”

What an accomplishment Su!! We are proud of you!

PIctured: Su Wright being given her award by Director of Regional Community Outreach, Valerie Rhoades.
